	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, a good starting race for the Ranger is definately the Wood Elf. You will decide whatever is right for you, but I started with the Half Elf in Qeynos and found leveling to be hard and skills rose slow.<BR>
With the Wood Elf you immediately get the skills, Hide and Forage, at level 1, instead of having to wait until level 3 for forage and level 20 for Hide like you would with the other races.<BR>
You will start in Kelethin as a Wood Elf, and the area around the Tree City is great for quickly raising up to level 4 or 5. After 4 or 5 I would look into getting into a group that can take you to Kaladim and the port.<BR>
From there jump on a boat to Freeport and head to Rivervale. Get someone to bind you in Rivervale. The monsters out in Misty Thicket can get you up to level 9 in no time and you can travel back to Kelethin to fight the Orcs on better terms, and get some much deserved Ringmail.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#D6D1BE">	
		
	
			</font>
			<font face="Verdana" size="1"><b>
			<font color="black">--Submited by:&nbsp;
			<a href="mailto:maximus@stny.lrun.com">Kyodai</a></font> 
			<font color="black">On:&nbsp;05/15/1999 11:09:34 PM&nbsp;&nbsp;
			</font></b></font>
	
