	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Seeing as how the half elf Ranger is being neglected, I feel it's my duty to help rectify that situation. The life of a half elf Ranger begins in the Surefall Glade, north of Qeynos. Surefall is a nice quiet place that is rarely visited by anyone but Druids and Rangers. In many ways it is an ideal starting place.<BR>
<BR>
To begin with it is isolated. Since most new players start in Qeynos with it's multitude of guilds, the hunting outside the city gates can be quite crowded. This is not so of Surefall Glade. Surefall has excellent monsters in the nearby Qeynos hills that are ideal for the lower level characters. I would suggest starting with bats and rats, seeing as how the wolves and bears are protected. Once you've gone up a bit in levels you can try your hand at the vast number of decaying skeletons that prevail at night. it also has the advantage of being a small town. Which makes it easier to navigate for beginners.<BR>
<BR>
In between third and fifth level, you should begin to think about seeing the world. Qeynos is the place to go. In addition to having good slightly higher level hunting out side it's gates, Qeynos is very well populated. Home to a variety of shops, most anyting can be bought in Qeynos. This is also where you will begin to develop friendships and learn about the other classes.<BR>
<BR>
At around seventh level you may be wanting something more. Well, you're in luck. Blackburrow is a stone's throw from both Qeynos and Surefall Glade. Home to the rank gnolls, Blackburrow can support hunting for parties well into their twenties. But the upper levels contain beasties that can be handled by lower level adventurers.<BR>
<BR>
I've only made it to level 11 so I can't offer much advice past that, but the Surefall Glade starting location provides a fine balance of ease of use for a beginner and fine hunting opportunities.<BR>
<BR>
Remember, as a Ranger you should know where everything is. So explore a lot. People will come to you expecting you to know the way.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
	<tr>
		
