	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The Ranger is a rather balanced class. <BR>
Not specializing in just melee or pure magic <BR>
like all the other classes. Nor like the <BR>
shadowknight, confined to only attack magic, or <BR>
the paladin with only clerical magic, but both <BR>
offensive and defensive magic and good melee as well. <BR>
This make the Ranger very versital, as he can solo a fight,<BR>
using just plain melee attacks, and back himself<BR>
up with his attack magic for some extra damage. <BR>
Healing also makes the Ranger able to get back on <BR>
his feet much quicker,and be a minor healer in <BR>
his party. The Ranger can also equip a great deal <BR>
of armors and weapons. Although because a Ranger <BR>
can do so much, he is of course weaker in both <BR>
magic and pure melee but still strong enough to be <BR>
usefel magic user or fighter, and often gets the <BR>
abilitys or spells much later then other classes. <BR>
The Ranger is ideal for players who like a little<BR>
bit of everything.
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
